	<section class="sect-lnks">
		<h2><a href="http://www.canada.ca/en/services/jobs/find.html">Find a job</a></h2>
		<p>Find public and private sector job opportunities or hiring programs, apply or extend a work permit, get a Social Insurance Number, a criminal record check or security clearance.</p>
	</section>
	<section class="sect-lnks">
		<h2><a href="http://www.workingincanada.gc.ca/occupation_search-eng.do" rel="external">Explore careers</a></h2>
		<p>Explore career options, search occupations by Canadian city to find available jobs, learn about average wages, and job requirements.</p>
	</section>
	<section class="sect-lnks">
		<h2><a href="http://www.canada.ca/en/services/jobs/training.html">Training</a></h2>
		<p>Information on education, training, financial assistance and the skills needed to find and keep a job.</p>
	</section>
	<section class="sect-lnks">
		<h2><a href="http://www.workingincanada.gc.ca/content_pieces-eng.do?cid=3264" rel="external">For employers</a></h2>
		<p>Information and tools to help find, hire, train, retain workers and includes how to advertise job openings.</p>
	</section>
	<section class="sect-lnks">
		<h2><a href="http://www.canadabusiness.ca/eng/page/2856/" rel="external">Self-employment</a></h2>
		<p>Information and tools to help you plan and start a business and, includes how to name, register and finance a business, hire and pay employees.</p>
	</section>
	<section class="sect-lnks">
		<h2><a href="http://www.canada.ca/en/services/jobs/workplace.html">Workplace standards</a></h2>
		<p>Information about federal and provincial labour laws, workplace standards, federal health and safety standards and labour relations programs.</p>
	</section>
	<section class="sect-lnks">
		<h2><a href="http://www.canada.ca/en/services/jobs/pensions.html">Pensions & retirement</a></h2>
		<p>Information about employer and personal pensions, federal benefits and registered retirement savings plans and tools to help you plan for retirement.</p>
	</section>
	<section class="sect-lnks">
		<h2><a href="http://www.canada.ca/en/services/benefits/ei/index.html">Employment Insurance</a></h2>
		<p>Information about the Employment Insurance (<abbr>EI</abbr>) and related programs, includes how to apply for <abbr title="Employment Insurance">EI</abbr> online, submit a report, and instructions for employers on how to submit a worker's Record of Employment.</p>
	</section>
